The Parquet file is Snappy-compressed and dictionary-encoded, so I decoded it locally from the file metadata. The first screen shows very strong dependency-specific signals, especially `feature_009` for `dependency_BRAF`, `feature_022` for `dependency_EGFR`, `feature_024` for `dependency_ERBB2`, `feature_014` for `dependency_KRAS`, `feature_027` for `dependency_RIT1`, and a much stronger KIF18A signal in colorectal/high-`feature_028` subgroups.
